ampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_lmhRW3nQLIM4R6rtiaQxyzGG", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the `methylKit` library in R.\\n2. Read the `input/mk_raw.rds` file to get the `methylRawList` object.\\n3. Apply the `filterByCoverage` function with `lo.count=3` and `hi.perc=99.9` to filter the data.\\n4. Normalize the coverage using the `normalizeCoverage` function with `method='median'.\\n5. Save the normalized object to `output/mk_filt_norm.rds`.\\n6. Calculate per-sample statistics: `n_CpGs`, `mean_mCpG`, `mean_coverage`, and `median_coverage`.\\n7. Write these statistics to `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv`.\\n8. Verify the existence of `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (619 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_lmhRW3nQLIM4R6rtiaQxyzGG"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ugfP9FaDJpIUjh2LJ9auo8DM", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Step 2: Read the methylRawList object\\nmk_raw <- readRDS('input/mk_raw.rds')\\n\\n# Step 3: Apply filterByCoverage\\nmk_filt <- filterByCoverage(mk_raw, lo.count=3, hi.perc=99.9)\\n\\n# Step 4: Normalize coverage\\nmk_norm <- normalizeCoverage(mk_filt, method='median')\\n\\n# Step 5: Save the normalized object\\nsaveRDS(mk_norm, 'output/mk_filt_norm.rds')\\n\\n# St