s not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given `input/mk_raw.rds` (methylRawList, methylKit). Apply\n`filterByCoverage(lo.count=3, hi.perc=99.9)` then\n`normalizeCoverage(method='median')`; save the normalized object to\n`output/mk_filt_norm.rds` and write a per-sample stats TSV to\n`output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` (columns `sample, n_CpGs, mean_mCpG,\nmean_coverage, median_coverage`).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: filt_norm_stats.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_lmhRW3nQLIM4R6rtiaQxyzGG", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the `methylKit` library in R.\\n2. Read the `input/mk_raw.rds` file to get the `methylRawList` object.\\n3. Apply the `filterByCoverage` function with `lo.count=3` and `hi.perc=99.9` to filter the data.\\n4. Normalize the coverage using the `normalizeCoverage` function with `method='median'.\\n5. Save the normalized object to `output/mk_filt_norm.rds`.\\n6. Calculate per-sample statistics: `n_CpGs`, `mean_mCpG`, `mean_coverage`, and `median_coverage`.\\n7. Write these statistics to `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv`.\\n8. Verify the existence of `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (619 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_lmhRW3nQLIM4R6rtiaQxyzGG"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ugfP9FaDJpIUjh2LJ9auo8DM", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Step 2: Read the methylRawList object\\nmk_raw <- readRDS('input/mk_raw.rds')\\n\\n# Step 3: Apply filterByCoverage\\nmk_filt <- filterByCoverage(mk_raw, lo.count=3, hi.perc=99.9)\\n\\n# Step 4: Normalize coverage\\nmk_norm <- normalizeCoverage(mk_filt, method='median')\\n\\n# Step 5: Save the normalized object\\nsaveRDS(mk_norm, 'output/mk_filt_norm.rds')\\n\\n# Step 6: Calculate per-sample statistics\\nstats_list <- lapply(mk_norm, function(sample) {\\n  n_CpGs <- length(sample)\\n  mean_mCpG <- mean(getMethylationStats(sample, plot=FALSE)$methylation)\\n  coverage_stats <- getCoverageStats(sample, plot=FALSE)\\n  mean_coverage <- mean(coverage_stats$coverage)\\n  median_coverage <- median(coverage_stats$coverage)\\n  return(c(n_CpGs, mean_mCpG, mean_coverage, median_coverage))\\n})\\n\\n# Convert list to data frame\\nstats_df <- do.call(rbind, stats_list)\\ncolnames(stats_df) <- c('n_CpGs', 'mean_mCpG', 'mean_coverage', 'median_coverage')\\n\\n# Add sample names\\nstats_df <- data.frame(sample=names(mk_norm), stats_df)\\n\\n# Step 7: Write statistics to TSV\\nwrite.table(stats_df, 'output/filt_norm_stats.tsv', sep='\\\\t', row.names=FALSE, quote=FALSE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\nmethylation statistics per base\nsummary:\n   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. \n   0.00   25.00   43.67   48.40   75.00  100.00 \npercentiles:\n        0%        10%        20%        30%        40%        50%      