put/mk_filt_norm.rds`.\\n6. Calculate per-sample statistics: `n_CpGs`, `mean_mCpG`, `mean_coverage`, and `median_coverage`.\\n7. Write these statistics to `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv`.\\n8. Verify the existence of `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\\n\\n### Debugging Steps\\n- Fix the calculation of statistics by ensuring the correct extraction of numeric values from the methylation and coverage statistics.\\n- Ensure that the data frame is constructed correctly with appropriate dimensions.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (858 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_mL3SzaGdAh7diXxuA8BF2jHW"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_IIeLpao7zxIaLlvkEjQwtnDu", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Step 2: Read the methylRawList object\\nmk_raw <- readRDS('input/mk_raw.rds')\\n\\n# Step 3: Apply filterByCoverage\\nmk_filt <- filterByCoverage(mk_raw, lo.count=3, hi.perc=99.9)\\n\\n# Step 4: Normalize coverage\\nmk_norm <- normalizeCoverage(mk_filt, method='median')\\n\\n# Step 5: Save the normalized object\\nsaveRDS(mk_norm, 'output/mk_filt_norm.rds')\\n\\n# Step 6: Calculate per-sample statistics\\nstats_list <- lapply(mk_norm, function(sample) {\\n  n_CpGs <- length(sample)\\n  methylation_stats <- getMethylationStats(sample, plot=FALSE)\\n  mean_mCpG <- mean(methylation_stats$percent.methylation)\\n  coverage_stats <- getCoverageStats(sample, plot=FALSE)\\n  mean_coverage <- mean(coverage_stats$coverage)\\n  median_coverage <- median(coverage_stats$coverage)\\n  return(c(n_CpGs, mean_mCpG, mean_coverage, median_coverage))\\n})\\n\\n# Convert list to data frame\\nstats_df <- do.call(rbind, stats_list)\\ncolnames(stats_df) <- c('n_CpGs', 'mean_mCpG', 'mean_coverage', 'median_coverage')\\n\\n# Add sample names\\nstats_df <- data.frame(sample=names(mk_norm), stats_df